    "title": "Critical Fortinet FortiSandbox Vulnerability Enables Code Execution Attacks",
    "description": "A critical security flaw in Fortinet&#8217;s FortiSandbox platform is putting enterprise networks at serious risk, allowing unauthenticated attackers to execute arbitrary code or commands remotely, with no credentials required. Fortinet disclosed the vulnerability on May 12, 2026, under the identifier CVE-2026-26083 (FG-IR-26-136), assigning it a CVSSv3 score of 9.1, placing it firmly in the critical [&#8230;] \n The post  Critical Fortinet FortiSandbox Vulnerability Enables Code Execution Attack",
